Because of this it's not too handy.</li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong>1C: </strong>In some cases, you may get a carry, in which the result is wrong. If we take this carry and add it to the result, we get our answer. This makes 1C easy in some cases, but not in all.</li></ul><p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/XBaCCNv.png" width="341"></p><p><br></p><ul><li><strong>2C: </strong>Here you'll always get the right result, if there is a carry you can simply ignore it:</li></ul><p><img src="https://i.imgur.com/jsDQZ8D.png" width="341"></p><p><br></p><h2 id="arithmetic-with-2c">Arithmetic with 2C</h2><h3 id="addition">Addition</h3><p>We do not need special adders, a normal binary adder can be used to add two 2C integers. We just need to ignore the carries.</p><p><br></p><p>This can be denoted as <span class="ql-formula" data-value="s=ADD\left(x,y,0\right)">﻿<span contenteditable="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>s</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>D</mi><mi>D</mi><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>y</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mn>0</mn><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">s=ADD\left(x,y,0\right)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.43056em; An overflow occurs when these carry-outs have different values. </p><p>In addition, an overflow can occur when both operands are the same sign, and after addition it doesn't.</p><p><br></p><p>So we can check overflow in 2 ways:</p><ul><li>Check the signs of the two inputs and the output. If the inputs have the same sign and the output has a different sign =&gt; overflow. Downside: you can only check for overflow after the calculation</li><li>Looking at the carry-out from the MSB position <span class="ql-formula" data-value="c_n">﻿<span contenteditable="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>c</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">c_n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.58056em;
